text: Prindle is an unincorporated community in Skamania County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Prindle was established in 1909, and remained in operation until 1938. The community was named after Ernest Hinsdale Prindle, an early settler. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Skamania County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Prindle, Washington
